\pard\plain \tx0\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Magic is the single most important force within the Drakon Confederacy. It is the true power from which all other authority derives. And it is an absolute necessity to nurture and advance its power as much as possible for the security of the entire world. For just beyond the world, in the void between universes, dwell monstrosities that seek to destroy everything they encounter. These beings are manifestations of madness and decay, of entropy and chaos itself, and work tirelessly to eliminate all order from the cosmos, to return it all to primordial non-existence. It is only the power of Magic that gives the sentient races the ability to fight back against such Eldritch abominations. And at the pinnacle of mortal magic stand the Dragons. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Dragons are not a normal creature of the natural world. Dragons do not reproduce the way other creatures do. Every Dragon begins its existence as part of one of the other sentient, magic using races, like humanity, elves, or a myriad of others. Some few of these races are born with a dragon-seed in their soul, giving them the potential to become Dragons, given time and good fortune. Becoming a Dragon is no easy process, it requires the accumulation of immense magical power, usually through the study and practice of magic over decades if not centuries. Such accumulation of power causes the dragon-seed within their soul to sprout and grow, changing them over time into Dragons in body and soul.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Every sentient being in this world has some potential to use magic, whether they bear a dragon-seed or not. The Drakon Confederacy has developed a means to safely and quickly assess this potential, a tool they call a Mage Stone. The one to be tested picks up the Mage Stone and holds it near their mouth, breathing out ten slow breaths onto the stone. Each breath causes to the stone to pulse with a slight glow, the light growing steadier and brighter with each breath. The color of the glow reveals the potential of the person being tested. The colors the stone produces are the colors of flame, the hotter the flame colors, the greater magical potential of the person. The scale ranges from the dark, cool reds, to ambers and oranges, yellows and whites, to blue and even violet at the hottest end of the scale.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Those with the weakest potential, the darkest red colors on the scale, lack the power to wield magic with any degree of skill or power and are never trained. Ambers and weaker oranges are not accepted for training on their first testing but all oranges are trained if it is their second testing.  The additional maturity gained in the intervening years serves to improve the odds of the trainees reaching graduation even if their potential has not developed to a higher level during that time. Bright oranges, yellows, and whites are always trained and few with potential of white or higher fail to find themselves pulled into a Noble House by the end of their training.  Blues are rare and are always trained to joined the Battlemages, the most powerful of various guilds. Violets are so rare as to be considered legendary because that color indicates an activated dragon-seed, which is to say one that has begun to sprout, however slightly. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Unfortunately, only the Dragons know the truth about dragon-seeds. The Collegium Arcanus, where the mages are trained to use and explore their powers, merely believe that any sufficiently powerful mage can become a Dragon. The Dragons, however, can sense a dragon-seed whenever they are close enough to its bearer. For this reason, Dragons always take those who bear a dragon-seed under their wing and mentor them. They also tend to mentor an assortment of powerful Battlemages as well so as to mask the presence of actual dragon-seeds.}
