\par\pard\plain \tx0\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Magic is powered by breath. Breath which overflows with the vital energies of the breather. The same breath which fuels muscles and movement and life. Ergo the more exhausted a person is from exertion, the less magic they can muster. Magic can be breathed into specially prepared objects: foci, relics, and artifacts, to power their magical abilities or it can be breathed into spell forms created by skilled mages in order to manifest supernatural effects. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Spell forms come in two basic types: temporary constructs or permanent structures. The temporary constructs tend to be mental in nature, an envisioning of the geometric figures and runes that shape the power of magic into a manifest effect. Permanent structures are much more flexible in many ways, they can be tattooed on flesh, carved in stone, forged as a metal object, or any number of other physical creations. The advantage of such things is two-fold: they are faster to activate than a mental spell form and they do not require a complete understanding of the form itself to use. All spell forms have a common drawback, however, breathing magic into an incomplete or incorrectly formed results in backlash. Backlash generally manifests as the completely uncontrolled release of magical energy. This manifestation is usually an explosive process and becomes more dangerous the more energy is breathed into the form.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Breath itself comes in two basic forms: mortal breath and dragon breath. Mortal breath is less potent and less dense in magical energy. All sapient, non-dragon, lifeforms possess mortal breath, though the energy density of such breath varies with the power of the being breathing. Dragon breath, on the other hand, is far more powerful. It\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s weakest degree of energy density is orders of magnitudes more potent than the strongest of mortal breath. Dragon breath is so dense with magical energy that it can be shaped into an exhalation of elemental energy with nothing more than thought and will. This is how Dragons breath out flames, ice, lightning or toxic gas at need. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Those possessed of dragon seeds possess a small amount of dragon breath from the moment that the seed begins to sprout. As the seed sprouts and grows toward maturity, more and more of their mortal breath become dragon breath. At first, they may not understand this small well of intense power, but the process of becoming a dragon comes with a slowly growing understanding of what is happening to the nascent dragon. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Foci, relics, and artifacts are the product of the artificer\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s trade and represent three different grades of enchanted object. Foci, the simplest kind, contain a single spell form of relatively low complexity. They store no magic of their own, and are limited in their usefulness as a result. Relics are far more varied than foci, often containing multiple spell forms of differing complexity. Many relics possess a small to moderate reservoir that the wielder can breath power into and that keeps the relic operating without the active attention of the user. As such, relics can produce more passive effects than foci. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Artifacts are the more powerful and rarest of magical items and are yet more complex than even the most potent of relics. The spell forms and enchantments laid on an artifact are layered to create effects far beyond what is possible in foci or relics and an artifact contains a much, much larger reservoir of power. A reservoir that is, in many cases, several times larger than the breath capacity of even the most powerful of mages. The bearers of such things often spent as much as a few hours each day breathing power back into the reservoirs of their artifacts to keep them topped up. The most common artifacts are the fantastic battle armor worn by the most powerful of Battlemages. Armor which is crafted by the Dragons for their most power weapons in the battle against the void-dwellers. Since these suits are powerful and difficult to destroy they become heirlooms within the families of those blessed with such gifts, with new suits created whenever the Dragons need to elevate a new Warlord.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 While Warlord armor is relatively common as artifacts go, no more than a dozen or so might exist within even the oldest states of the Confederacy, and even fewer in the younger states. Other artifacts tend to be unique or nearly unique and vary greatly. Each artifact is crafted by a master artificer and many represent the culmination of a lifetime of pursuing the pinnacle of their craft. The most powerful artifacts tend to be infused with the very life of the crafter, who often die in the process of quickening the item. Only an artifact crafted by a Dragon-king can surpass such creations in power.}
