\par\pard\plain \tx0\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Within the Confederacy, all children are tested on their 13th and 19th birthdays for mage spark. This is because the breath and potential of a child grows within them from birth, but slowly until the beginning of puberty. The 13th birthday is the earliest time when that potential power might have crossed a threshold to be suitable for training and very few children are taken at this age for the Collegium. The first testing is mostly to establish a baseline of the child\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s potential. The second testing, and the difference between it and the first testing, tell the true story of the child\u8217\'92s potential as a mage. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 A dragon seed is only detectable by the test if it has already begun to sprout. This is incredibly rare at the first testing, but usually indicates a Dragon with the potential to become a full Dragon-King in their own right.}
